Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

---

**1. Register the route (AppShell.xaml.cs)**

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

---

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage (two approaches)**

```csharp
// Approach A ‚Äî pass the ID as a query string
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B ‚Äî pass the full Product object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

---

**3. Receive data in ProductDetailsViewModel**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A ‚Äî string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using ProductId...
        }

        // Approach B ‚Äî full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

---

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page**

```xml
<!-- ProductDetailsPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailsViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <Label Text="{Binding Product.Name}" />
</ContentPage>
```

> **Tip:** If you use dependency injection, register both the page and ViewModel in `MauiProgram.cs` and let the constructor inject the VM instead of creating it in XAML.

**Key differences:**
| | Query string (`?productId=`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| Data type | Strings only | Any object |
| Serialization | Automatic URI encoding | None (passed by reference) |
| Best for | Simple IDs, filters | Complex/large objects |

Always `await` the `GoToAsync` call to avoid race conditions.
